President Muhamamdu Buhari has called on his supporters to stop campaigning for him and respect the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) timetable on elections campaign. The President, in a statement signed by Presidential Spokesman, Femi Adesina, called on his supporters “not to jump the gun” by engaging in campaigns, ahead of the 2019 Presidential election The President however commended his supporters for their massive support nationwide adding that “ We appreciate our massive supporters nationwide, and urge them to exercise restraint till the race commences officially as stipulated by law.” The President noted that “While a chronicle of the achievements of the administration is in order now, outright canvasing may amount to jumping the gun. He declared that this administration is committed to due process and scrupulous respect for rules, law and order. The President had observed that some fervent supporters of his supporters have begun what may be interpreted as political campaigns in their advocacies and advertisements in the mass media. “We appreciate their enthusiasm, borne out of desire to garner support for an administration that is actuated by nothing else, other than service for motherland, but we hereby appeal for patience, so that the game can be played according to the rules.
“The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has a timetable for political campaigns, and we urge committed supporters round the country (and beyond) to be mindful of such.
He assured that there “will be ample time ahead to trumpet the good works of the Buhari administration, and solicit re-election, all for the good of our country and her people.” 